<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Afoot" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Afoot,</orth> 1) on foot: <cit><quote>walked ten mile a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 17</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 387</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.7.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 7, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.5.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 5, 21</bibl>.<lb />2) concerning infantry: <cit><quote>of what strength they are a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls IV, 3, 181</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) in motion and action: <cit><quote>the matter being a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.5.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 5, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the game is a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.278" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 278</bibl></cit> (hunted up, started); cf. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 1, 32</bibl>. <cit><quote>these rebels now a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 9</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.211" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.2.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 2, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.265" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 265</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.185" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 185</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.3.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 3, 51</bibl>. <cit><quote>to keep base life a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.218" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 218</bibl></cit> (to sustain). <emph>well a.</emph> == in good health: <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 29</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>